Cape Town - SAPS arrested a suspect with gang ties in Thornton in an operation conducted by members of the Major Offences Reaction Team and Crime Intelligence. The SAPS units reacted on information and conducted a search operation at a residence in Tecoma Crescent Thornton on Tuesday night. The operation resulted in the arrest of a 45-year-old suspect affiliated to a local Cape Flats gang. An assortment of drugs comprising dagga, crack and ecstasy tablets were confiscated as well as a 9mm Glock pistol, a 38 Special revolver and 58 rounds of ammunition. The suspect is detained on charges of dealing in drugs and a contravention of the Firearms Act (Act 60/2000) and is due to make a court appearance once he has been charged. argusnews@inl.co.za Cape Argus